&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Of course, you can only get the element after the component mounts. So, if you need to use it right when the page loads, use the &lt;code>onMounted()&lt;/code> function.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Learning Vue</title><link>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/196/</link><pubDate>Fri, 15 Nov 2024 20:48:29 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/196/</guid><description>&lt;div class="notice ">&lt;strong>📢&lt;/strong> This article was translated by gemini-3-flash-preview
